As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 284 people, 100 households, and 79 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|151.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 103 housing units at an average density of {{convert|54.9|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 92.25% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1.41% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1.41% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 4.93% from two or more races.

There were 100 households, out of which 44.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 72.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 3.0% had a female householder with no husband present, and 21.0% were non-families. 17.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 5.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.84 and the average family size was 3.24.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 31.7% under the age of 18, 6.3% from 18 to 24, 25.0% from 25 to 44, 31.0% from 45 to 64, and 6.0% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 36 years. For every 100 females, there were 95.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 104.2 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $56,375, and the median income for a family was $57,125. Males had a median income of $48,000 versus $19,519 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $24,823. None of the families and 2.0% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]].

